# Canonical App URL (Optional)
# Set this to your custom domain or canonical URL for production deployment
# Leave empty to use the default canister subdomain (canister-id.ic0.app)
#
# Examples:
#   VITE_CANONICAL_APP_URL=https://visiongalaxy.app
#   VITE_CANONICAL_APP_URL=https://mycompany.com/society-app
#   VITE_CANONICAL_APP_URL=https://app.visiongalaxy.com
#
# When set:
# - Users accessing via ic0.app/?canisterId=... will be redirected to this URL
# - PWA manifest start_url and scope will use this URL
# - Supports custom domains with or without base paths
# - The deployment script (ic-deploy-with-retry.sh) will display this as your live URL
#
# When empty:
# - Users are redirected to canister subdomain (canister-id.ic0.app)
# - PWA manifest uses relative paths
# - The deployment script will display the default ic0.app URL
#
# Usage:
# 1. Create a file named .env in the frontend/ directory
# 2. Add your canonical URL: VITE_CANONICAL_APP_URL=https://yourdomain.com
# 3. Deploy: ./frontend/deploy/ic-deploy-with-retry.sh
# 4. The script will automatically load this value and display it as your live URL
#
# Alternatively, export it before deployment:
#   export VITE_CANONICAL_APP_URL=https://yourdomain.com
#   ./frontend/deploy/ic-deploy-with-retry.sh
#
# Note: Ensure your custom domain is properly configured to point to your IC canister
# See: https://internetcomputer.org/docs/current/developer-docs/production/custom-domain/
VITE_CANONICAL_APP_URL=
